<glossary>
<definition id="fs-idm252399552">
<term>auditing</term>
<meaning id="fs-idm255439280">process of ensuring activities are carried out as intended or designed</meaning>
</definition>
<definition id="fs-idm267161616">
<term>consulting</term>
<meaning id="fs-idm227124000">process of giving advice or guidance on financial and nonfinancial impact of a course of action</meaning>
</definition>
<definition id="fs-idm233279120">
<term>cost accounting</term>
<meaning id="fs-idm537825968">recording and tracking of costs in the manufacturing process</meaning>
</definition>
<definition id="fs-idm203402560">
<term>governmental accounting</term>
<meaning id="fs-idm267961168">process of tracking the inflows and outflows of taxpayer funds using prescribed standards</meaning>
</definition>
<definition id="fs-idm259352336">
<term>not-for-profit (NFP) accounting</term>
<meaning id="fs-idm479223824">including charities, universities, and foundations, helps ensure that donor funds are used for the intended mission of the not-for-profit entity</meaning>
</definition>
</glossary>
